The paper deals with the problem of throughput allocation in IEEE 802.11 Wireless LANs, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of proportional fairness (PF) criterion, which is a well-known concept in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper presents simulation results, which suggests the use of multimedia applications (cs.MM) and system-level design (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a modified PF criterion, which can be considered as a contribution to the field of performance evaluation and optimization (cs.PF).
